Bren school home / Graduate


ICS Graduate Student Affairs Office

The primary focus of the ICS Graduate Student Affairs Office is to assist students and faculty with University policies, procedures, and requirements related to ICS academic programs. The graduate staff coordinates the graduate admissions process, fellowships, and the graduate student review. It also handles the various forms and administrative functions relating to graduate students. 
Contact Information
Appointments:
Monday thru Thursday: 1 - 3:30pm (remote and in-person)
Friday: 1 - 3:30pm (remote only)
ICS Graduate Counselors are here to help with any questions or concerns you may have. We would love to meet with you. To book an appointment with an ICS Graduate Counselor, please email the corresponding program you are in or interested in below with the subject line “Appointment Request - Remote” or “Appointment Request - In-person.” You are also more than welcome to contact our phone line at (949) 824-5156 to request an appointment.
M.S. & Ph.D. students: gcounsel@ics.uci.edu
MCS students: mcs@ics.uci.edu
MSWE students: mswe@ics.uci.edu
MHCID students: mhcid@ics.uci.edu
MDS students: mds@ics.uci.edu
General Office E-mail: gcounsel@ics.uci.edu
Phone: (949) 824-5158
Fax: (949) 824-4163
Mailing Address: ICS Graduate Student Affairs, Donald Bren School of Information and Computer Sciences, ICS 2 200, UCI, CA, 92697

Graduate Student Affairs Staff
